burlap.oomdp.stochasticgames

Class SingleAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • burlap.oomdp.stochasticgames.SGAgentAction
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SingleStageNormalFormGame.NFGSingleAction, UniversalSingleAction

    public abstract class SingleAction
extends java.lang.Object
    A single action is an action specification for individual agents in a stochastic game. The single action specifies preconditions and any parameters that are required for it to operate. Like The Action class and PropositionalFunction class, SingleAction'o can also specify parameter order groups for parameter effect symmetry. See the PropositionalFunction class documentation for a larger discussion on parameter order groups. Unlike The Action class, SingleAction'o do not specify the actual transition dynamics, because transition dynamics in a stochastic game depend on the full joint action of all agents (that is, the SingleAction selected by each agent in the world).
    Author:
    James MacGlashan
